Dear Brian, Theresa,
We would like to migrate the hosting of the Inclign.Rivel environment on to=
 AWS (it is currently hosted on a non-cloud server in the UK).
We have found that passing security checks/audits with large customers is m=
uch easier when the platform is hosted on AWS and this architecture also al=
lows us to dedicate a virtual machine to each customer. This approach provi=
des an air gap between customers and also allows us to give the customer ac=
cess to their machine should they want to have it for transparency purposes=
. Our WISPs now reflect this approach so it would be good to also have Incl=
ign.Rivel switched over to be ready for customer questions.
In order to switch over we need you to create a new A record for Inclign.Ri=
vel for 18.223.117.78 .
Would it be possible for you to do this at 12 midday your time on Tuesday 1=
6th June? We need to take the old platform down whilst the hosting switches=
 over, so Inclign.Rivel will be unavailable for up to 48 hours (but probabl=
y mush less) whilst we do that. We would take the old host down and put up =
an "under maintenance, please check back later" sign should anyone land at =
the old host.
Theresa - we are suggesting Tuesday because recent user logs suggest that w=
e only get 1 or 2 reviews completed after that day on a usual week - and by=
 switching on Tuesday it gives us some time to make sure we are up and runn=
ing again for Friday.
If you have any questions please let me know. Otherwise if you could confir=
m that this will be possible we will set everything up for next Tuesday and=
 I will check back then to double check that we are co-ordinated.
Thanks and Regards
Chris

